com.radiantlogic.iddm.base

Class SchemaObject.SchemaObjectBuilder

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.radiantlogic.iddm.base.SchemaObject.SchemaObjectBuilder
  • Enclosing class:
    SchemaObject

    public static class SchemaObject.SchemaObjectBuilder
extends Object
    Builder class for creating SchemaObject instances with validation.

    This builder extends Lombok's generated builder to add custom validation logic for required fields and constraints. It ensures that SchemaObject instances are created in a valid state and provides meaningful error messages for invalid inputs.

    Usage Examples: 

    
 // Minimal schema object
 SchemaObject simple = SchemaObject.builder()
     .name("users")
     .objectClass("person")
     .build();
 
 // Complete schema object with all options
 SchemaObject complete = SchemaObject.builder()
     .name("user_accounts")
     .objectClass("userAccount")
     .owner("HR Department")
     .baseTable("tbl_users")
     .candidateKeyName("username")
     .candidateKeys(Collections.singletonList("username"))
     .primaryKeys(Arrays.asList("id", "tenant_id"))
     .fields(Arrays.asList(
         Field.builder().name("id").type(Field.Type.STRING).build(),
         Field.builder().name("username").type(Field.Type.STRING).build()
     ))
     .build();

      • candidateKeys

        public SchemaObject.SchemaObjectBuilder candidateKeys(@NonNull
                                                      @NonNull List<String> candidateKeys$value)
        Sets the candidate keys for this schema object with validation.

        This method overrides Lombok's generated builder method to add validation that ensures the candidate keys list is not empty.

        Lombok Builder Implementation Notes:
        When using @Builder with @Builder.Default fields, Lombok generates internal builder fields with specific naming conventions:

        • candidateKeys$value - stores the actual field value
        • candidateKeys$set - tracks whether the field was explicitly set

        To properly override a Lombok-generated builder method while maintaining compatibility with the default value mechanism, we must:

        1. Use the $value field name to store the actual value
        2. Set the $set flag to true to indicate explicit assignment

        Without setting candidateKeys$set = true, Lombok would ignore our custom value and use the @Builder.Default value instead (empty list).

        Parameters:
        candidateKeys$value - The list of candidate key names (must not be empty)
        Returns:
        This builder instance for method chaining
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the candidate keys list is empty
        Implementation Note:
        The parameter name candidateKeys$value matches Lombok's internal naming convention for builder fields with default values.
